Exercise 10 — Continuous Integration (exp 4)
1. Create and build a freestyle project in Jenkins using your GitHub repo
○ Jenkins → New Item → Freestyle project → Give name → OK.
○ Under Source Code Management choose Git, provide repo URL and
credentials if private.
○ Under Build add Invoke top-level Maven targets with clean package or
set Execute shell with mvn clean package.
○ Save → Build Now.
2. Check Console Output
○ Click build number → Console Output → verify BUILD SUCCESS and test
logs.
○ This demonstrates CI: code is fetched, compiled, tested automatically by
Jenkins on build trigger.
